BEGIN_PGML

During the delivery phase of fastball pitch, the arm internally rotates at the shoulder. The angular velocity of this internal rotation peaks at [`[$omega]`] [`rad/s`]. At this instant, the elbow angle is [`90^{\circ}`], so the angular velocity of the forearm is also [`[$omega]`] [`rad/s`]. The baseball in the pitcher's hand is [`[$d]`] [`cm`] from this axis of rotation through the shoulder joint. At this instant the linear velocity of the baseball is [`[$v]`] [`m/s`].

*a)* How much of the baseball's total linear velocity is due to the [`[$omega]`] [`rad/s`] angular velocity of the forearm?

[_____]{"$p"} [`%`]  

*b)* What is the centripetal acceleration of the baseball at this instant?

[`a_r=`] [_____]{"$a"} [`m/s^2`]  

*c)* How large is the force exerted by the pitcher on the baseball to cause this acceleration? The baseball's mass is [`[$m]`] [`g`].

[`F=`] [_____]{"$f"} [`N`]  

END_PGML

